Language name: HUAVE
Language number: 6716
Alternate names: 
Classification: North American, Penutian
Comments: San Francisco del Mar dialect.  Huave is spoken 
in southeastern coastal areas of Oaxaca, Mexico.  "Dental" 
consonants are palatalized before front vowels or glides; 
word-final palato-alveolars are analyzed by Suarez (1975) 
as followed by a semi-vowel.  Huave has a two-level tone 
system with little functional load.  Vowels can be long 
and short.

Sources: 

Kreger, G.A.S. and Scharfe de Stairs, E.F.  1981.  
Diccionario Huave de San Mateo del Mar.  Serie de 
Vocabularios y Diccionarios Indigenas "Mariano Silva y 
Aceves", Num. 24.  Instituto Linguistico de Verano, 
Mexico, D.F.

Suarez, J.A.  1975.  Estudios Huaves.  Coleccion 
cientifica: Linguistica 22.  Instituto Nacional de 
Antropologia e Historia, Mexico.